com.sri.ai.grinder.core.solver

Class AbstractModelCountingWithPropagatedLiteralsImportedFromSatisfiabilityStepSolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.grinder.core.solver.AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver
      • com.sri.ai.grinder.core.solver.AbstractModelCountingWithPropagatedLiteralsImportedFromSatisfiabilityStepSolver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExpressionLiteralSplitterStepSolver, ExpressionStepSolver, LiteralSplitterStepSolver<Expression>, StepSolver<Expression>, java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ModelCountingOfSingleVariableEqualityConstraintStepSolver, ModelCountingOfSingleVariablePropositionalConstraintStepSolver

    @Beta
public abstract class AbstractModelCountingWithPropagatedLiteralsImportedFromSatisfiabilityStepSolver
extends AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver
    An abstract step solver for model counting step solvers.

    It extends AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver and provides propagated literals and propagated CNF identical to the ones provided by the satisfiability step solver, which is obtained through the theory's Theory.getSingleVariableConstraintSatisfiabilityStepSolver(SingleVariableConstraint, Context). However, it is important that the satisfiability step solver provided by the theory be an instance of AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver, because getPropagatedCNF(Context) is delegated to the satisfiability step solver's AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver.getPropagatedCNF(Context) method. An error is thrown if this assumption is violated.

    This class already defines that the model count is zero if the constraint is not satisfiable according to the satisfiability step solver due to propagated literals and propagated CNF not being satisfied by the context. Extensions still need to provide methods to compute the final solution when propagated literals and propagated CNF are satisfied.
